The paper focuses on text-to-image synthesis, which is a sub-domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses a generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of a text encoder, which is a common tool in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the creation of a dataset, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR).
